.\" docs/man/meow-config.5
.TH MEOW-CONFIG 5 "2025-09-19" "meowg1k" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
meow-config \- configuration for the \fBmeow\fR CLI (YAML)
.SH SYNOPSIS
Configuration is read from YAML files with the following precedence:
.IP "1." 3
Project config: \fB./.meowg1k/config.yaml\fR
.IP "2."
User config: \fB~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml\fR
.PP
Command-line flags always override configuration values.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBmeow\fR CLI uses layered YAML configuration to define defaults
and reusable tasks for AI generation. Settings can be declared at project
and/or user level and are merged in the order described above
(project overrides user).
.SH FORMAT
YAML, UTF-8.
.PP
Top-level section for generation:
.PP
.nf
generate:
  defaultProvider: "gemini"          # "gemini", "nebius", or "llama"
  defaultModel: "gemini-2.5-flash"   # default model for Gemini/Nebius
  defaultTimeout: "5m"               # Go duration, e.g. "30s", "2m", "1h"
  tasks:                             # reusable commands invoked via -t/--task
    <task-name>:
      provider: "gemini" | "nebius" | "llama"
      model: "gemini-2.5-pro"        # optional; ignored when provider=llama
      llamaBaseURL: "http://127.0.0.1:8080"  # required when provider=llama
      systemPrompt: "High-level instruction"
      userPrompt: "Main prompt; stdin may be appended"
.fi
.SH KEYS
.TP
.B generate.defaultProvider
Provider for generation: \fBgemini\fR, \fBnebius\fR (cloud), or \fBllama\fR
(local). Default: \fBgemini\fR.
.TP
.B generate.defaultModel
Model for Gemini/Nebius AI Studio provider (e.g. \fBgemini-2.5-flash\fR).
Ignored for \fBllama\fR.
.TP
.B generate.defaultTimeout
Timeout as Go duration (e.g. \fB5m\fR). Applies to the whole request.
.TP
.B generate.tasks
A map of reusable tasks. Each task supports:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\fBprovider\fR: \fBgemini\fR, \fBnebius\fR, or \fBllama\fR
.IP \[bu]
\fBmodel\fR: Gemini/Nebius AI Studio model (ignored for llama)
.IP \[bu]
\fBllamaBaseURL\fR: base URL for llama.cpp (required for llama)
.IP \[bu]
\fBsystemPrompt\fR: system instruction
.IP \[bu]
\fBuserPrompt\fR: user prompt (stdin may be appended)
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for the Gemini provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_NEBIUS_API_KEY
API key for the Nebius AI Studio provider.
.SH MERGE RULES
Configs are merged with project taking precedence over user. Absent keys inherit
from lower precedence or built-in defaults. Flags always win over config.
.SH EXAMPLES
Minimal user config:
.PP
.nf
generate:
  defaultProvider: "gemini"
  defaultModel: "gemini-2.5-flash"
  defaultTimeout: "5m"
.fi
.PP
Project config with tasks:
.PP
.nf
generate:
  tasks:
    pytest-gemini:
      provider: "gemini"
      model: "gemini-2.5-pro"
      systemPrompt: "You are an expert Python TDD developer."
      userPrompt: "Write a complete pytest test file for the following code."
    security-audit:
      provider: "gemini"
      model: "gemini-2.5-pro"
      systemPrompt: "You are a senior security auditor."
      userPrompt: "Identify vulnerabilities and risky patterns."
    refactor-llama:
      provider: "llama"
      llamaBaseURL: "http://127.0.0.1:8080"
      systemPrompt: "You write clean, performant Rust."
      userPrompt: "Refactor for clarity and speed."
.fi
.PP
Usage:
.PP
.nf
cat app.py   | meow g -t pytest-gemini
cat server.js| meow g -t security-audit
meow g -P llama -u http://127.0.0.1:8080 -p "Summarize"
.fi
